game_information {
   game_name = "The Red Soldier";
   game_version = "0.3.0";
   game_shortname = "CHPuzzleXX";
   written_by = "Manda Whitney and Dan Egnor";
   uuid = "c6f4ccca-2f7f-4e4e-940f-ba5633fb86e1";
   year_of_release = "2020";
   short_synopsis = "Part of the 2020 Cryptex Hunt";
}

themes {
   t: theme {
      colors status_bar_pen="0" status_bar_paper="15";
      screen status_bar_padding_horz="1" padding_horz="1";
      status_bar {:header_text;}
      system_messages prompt=">> " question_prompt_char="Your answer? ";
      theme_settings layout="SB G LOCK D";
   }
}

booleans {
   day1_checkin_attempted: boolean "false";
   day1_checkin_done: boolean "false";
   day1_daniel_done: boolean "false";
   day1_daniel_met: boolean "false";
   day1_haley_done: boolean "false";
   day1_haley_met: boolean "false";
   day1_inventory_prompted: boolean "false";
   day1_joyce_done: boolean "false";
   day1_joyce_met: boolean "false";
   day1_lobby_visited: boolean "false";
   day1_nora_done: boolean "false";
   day1_nora_met: boolean "false";
   day1_slept: boolean "false";

   night1_awake: boolean "false";
   night1_kitchen_visited: boolean "false";
   night1_slept: boolean "false";

   day2_awake: boolean "false";
   day2_nora_scones: boolean "false";

   phone_buzzed: boolean "false";
   phone_read: boolean "false";

   sound_recorded: boolean "false";
   sound_played: boolean "false";
}

integers {
   clock_hour: integer "3";
}

strings {
   day1_checkin_code: string "";
}

#
# Rooms and layout
#

start_at = outside

locations {
   cellar: location {
      header = "Cellar";
      on_describe {
         :print "The cellar is a little damp and a lot dusty. There's a washroom to the <east<14>>, or you can go back <up<14>> to the main floor.";

         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "You hear soft clattering from somewhere upstairs.";
         }
      }
   }

   cellar_stairs: location {
      header = "Stairs to Cellar";
      on_describe {
         :print "A sketchy flight of stairs leads <down<14>> to the cellar from here, or you can go <east<14>> to the kitchen or <south<14>> to the dining room.";

         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "The clattering is definitely coming from the kitchen.";
         }
      }
   }

   dining_room: location {
      header = "Dining Room";
      on_describe {
         :if (!(night1_awake && !day2_awake)) {
            :print "The quaint pub style dining room feels warm and inviting. There is an <antique hutch<5>> in one corner with a <plaque<5>> on the front. You see the lobby to the <east<14>> and cellar stairs to the <north<14>>.";
         } :else {
            :print "You almost trip over a chair in the dark. You can still make out the <hutch<5>> and its <plaque<5>>. The lobby is <east<14>> and the cellar stairs to the <north<14>>.";

            :if (!night1_kitchen_visited) {
               :print "You hear clattering from a nearby room.";
            }
         }
      }
   }

   hallway_east: location {
      header = "Upstairs Hallway East";
      on_describe {
         :print "This is the east end of the hotel hallway. There's a <clock<5>> on the wall with a <plaque<5>> under it. The hallway leads <west<14>>, there's a locked guest room to the south, and stairs lead <down<14>> to the lobby.";

         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "The boards creak loudly under your feet. The clattering continues downstairs.";
         }
      }
   }

   hallway_west: location {
      header = "Upstairs Hallway West";
      on_describe {
         :print "This is the west end of the hotel hallway. Your own hotel room is to the <west<14>>, the hallway leads <east<14>>, and there's a locked guest room to the south.";

         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "There is another thump from downstairs, followed by clattering...";
         }
      }
   }

   hidden_room: location {
      header = "Hidden Cellar Room";
      on_describe {
         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "You hear soft clattering from somewhere upstairs.";
         }
      }
   }

   hotel_room: location {
      header = "Your Hotel Room";
      on_describe {
         :if (day1_slept && !night1_awake) {
            :set_true "night1_awake";
            :print "A large thump jolts you out of your sleep.";
            :print "You think nothing of it, and try to go back to sleep.";
            :press_any_key;
            :print "There is another thump. And then another. It seems to be coming from downstairs.";
            :print "Maybe you should check it out...";
            :return;
         }

         :if (night1_slept && !day2_awake) {
            :set_true "day2_awake";
            :print "You wake up. In the daylight the room is back to its cheery coziness.";
            :print "You have some time before the convention begins. Time to get some answers. Who does this button belong to? You should examine the staff and show them it. And what does this recording mean? You're sure people would be interested in hearing it.";
            :press_any_key;
            :redescribe;
            :return;
         }

         :print "Your guest room is small but sufficient, with a <hotel bed<5>> and the usual accessories. There's a hallway door to the <east<14>>.";

         :if (is_present "eerie_sound") {
            :print "You still hear that <eerie sound<5>> from the <vent<5>>...";
         }
      }
   }

   kitchen: location {
      header = "Hotel Kitchen";
      on_describe {
         :if (!(night1_awake && !day2_awake)) {
            :print "This is the inn's kitchen, cluttered with supplies and implements. Cellar stairs are to the <west<14>> and the lobby door to the <south<14>>.";
         } :else {
            :if (!night1_kitchen_visited) {
               :set_true "night1_kitchen_visited";
               :print "You hold your breath and tense up as you approach the kitchen door. The clattering sounds are very clear now. Your heart practically leaps out of your chest as you turn the doorknob...";
               :press_any_key;
               :print "The clattering stops the moment you enter the room. The single security light that is on illuminates the area just enough to reveal the damage.";
               :press_any_key;
            } :else {
               :print "This is the kitchen, but something is very strange.";
            }

            :print "Drawers seem to be wrenched open. Various forks and spoons are wedged in between the countertop and the wall. And on the cupboards, written in bright red, is a <message<5>>: \"GET OUT\". It drips off of the cupboards and onto the counter.";
         }
      }
   }

   lobby: location { 
      header = "Hotel Lobby";
      on_describe {
         :if (!day1_lobby_visited) {
            :set_true "day1_lobby_visited";
            :print "As you enter, your eyes adjust to the dim light of the Red Soldier Inn's lobby.";
         }

         :if (!(night1_awake && !day2_awake)) {
            :print "Despite the somewhat worn look, the lobby seems very welcoming. On the wall is an <oil painting<5>> with a <plaque<5>> under it. There are some <pamphlets<5>> on the lobby desk.";

            :if (day1_checkin_done) {
               :print "You can see a quaint little dining room to the <west<14>>, the hotel kitchen to the <north<14>>, and some rickety steps <up<14>> to the guest rooms. You could go back outside to the <east<14>>, but why would you?";
            }
         } :else {
            :print "The lobby seems far less inviting at night. You can still make out the <oil painting<5>>, <plaque<5>> and <pamphlets<5>>. You could make your way <west<14>> to the dining room, <north<14>> to the kitchen, or back <up<14>> to the guest rooms.";

            :if (!night1_kitchen_visited) {
               :print "The clattering is definitely coming from the kitchen.";
            }
         }
      }
   }

   outside: location {
      header = "Outside the Red Soldier";
      on_describe {
         :print "You approach a quaint but somewhat run down looking inn. A sign swings over the door: \"The Red Soldier\".";
         :print "It was a long bus ride to get here. You're just thankful there is a bed in your immediate future. You pick up your suitcase, and head in.";
         :press_any_key;
         :goto "lobby";
         :redescribe;
         :return;
      }
   }

   washroom: location {
      header = "Public Washroom";
      on_describe {
         :print "This is the inn's public washroom. You've seen better, but you've also seen a lot worse.";

         :if (night1_awake && !night1_kitchen_visited) {
            :print "You hear soft clattering from somewhere upstairs.";
         }
      }
   }
}

connections {
   from, direction, to = [
      cellar, east, washroom,
      cellar, south, hidden_room,
      cellar, up, cellar_stairs,
      
      cellar_stairs, east, kitchen,
      cellar_stairs, south, dining_room,

      dining_room, east, lobby,
      
      hallway_east, west, hallway_west,
      hallway_east, down, lobby,
      hallway_west, west, hotel_room,

      kitchen, south, lobby,
      
      lobby, east, outside,
   ]
}

barriers {
   stay_in_lobby_until_checked_in :block {
      block_when_not = "day1_checkin_done";
      message = "Maybe <TALK TO JOYCE<5>> before roaming around?";
   }

   do_not_go_outside :block {
      location = "outside";
      message = "It's cold and damp out there. No thanks!";
   }
}

#
# Objects, scenery and NPCs
#

objects {
   hotel_bed: scenery "hotel bed" at="hotel_room" conspicuous="false" msg="The bed looks soft and comfortable.";

   clock: scenery "wall clock" at="hallway_east" conspicuous="false";

   clock_plaque: scenery "plaque below the clock" at="hallway_east" conspicuous="false" msg="The plaque below the clock reads: \"This clock, owned by the late Captain Sunders himself, is a fine example of early 19th century craftsmanship. Unfortunately this particular clock no longer runs, so don't set your watch by it!\"";

   creepy_message: scenery "a message smeared on the cupboards" conspicuous="false";

   daniel: scenery "Daniel" at="cellar" conspicuous="false";
   
   eerie_sound: scenery "an eerie sound" conspicuous="false" msg="The sound is strange, distorted, and decidedly creepy. It might be words but it's too soft to make out.";

   fine_china: scenery "fine china" at="dining_room" conspicuous="false" msg="The fine china in the hutch doesn't look very interesting.";

   front_desk: scenery "the hotel front desk" at="lobby" conspicuous="false" msg="The front desk isn't fancy but it is solid. The nameplate says \"Joyce\" and looks like it doesn't get changed much.";
   
   haley: scenery "Haley" at="kitchen" conspicuous="false";

   heating_vent: scenery "a heating vent" at="hotel_room" conspicuous="false" msg="The heating vent looks totally ordinary, and you have no way to remove it.";
   
   hutch: scenery "an antique hutch" at="dining_room" conspicuous="false" msg="The hutch reminds you of something your parents inherited from your grandparents. Fine china sits on its shelves.";
   
   hutch_plaque: scenery "plaque on the hutch" at="dining_room" conspicuous="false" msg="The plaque on the hutch reads \"This hutch is one of the few surviving pieces belonging to Captain Sunders. Specially crafted for the inn, it has remained here in accordance with Sunders' will.";

   joyce: scenery "Joyce" at="lobby" conspicuous="false";
   
   mobile_phone: object "your mobile phone" at="inventory" msg="You will never let your beloved phone go!";
   
   nora: scenery "Nora" at="dining_room" conspicuous="false";
   
   oil_painting: scenery "oil painting" at="lobby" conspicuous="false" msg="The painting depicts a soldier in British Army uniform.";

   painting_plaque: scenery "plaque below the painting" at="lobby" conspicuous="false" msg="The plaque below the painting reads \"An original portrait of Captain Sunders, the original builder, owner, and now namesake of the Red Soldier inn. This was completed shortly before his death during the War of 1812.\"";

   pamphlet: object "an informational pamphlet" at="lobby" conspicuous="false" msg="The pamphlet details the history of the inn and the town. It seems the inn was originally built in the early 1800s by someone named Captain Sunders.";

   room_keys: object "your hotel room keys" msg="This hotel is old enough to have real room keys, not some newfangled swipey card.";

   shirt_button: object "a button you found with the creepy message" msg="This is a shirt button that seems to have fallen off someone's clothes.";

   voice_recorder: object "a voice recorder" msg="Daniel gave you this to record and amplify \"unusual\" noises, and you took it to humor him. You can use it to <RECORD SOUND<5>> and <PLAY SOUND<5>>.";

   washroom_light: scenery "Washroom light" at="washroom" conspicuous="false" msg="The half broken flickering bathroom light doesn't seem very interesting.";
}

vocabulary {
   :adjective / aliases=[cell, mobile]
   :adjective / aliases=[creepy, eerie, spooky, weird]

   :noun / aliases=[cell, mobile, phone]
   :noun / aliases=[dan, daniel]
   :noun / aliases=[hotel, inn]
   :noun / aliases=[noise, sound]
   :noun / aliases=[woman, lady]

   :verb / aliases=[chat, greet, say, speak, talk, tell]
   :verb / aliases=[checkin, register]
   :verb / aliases=[examine, inspect, look, search, read, check]
   :verb / aliases=[play, playback]
}

on_render {
   :if (day1_slept && !night1_slept) {
      :if (is_at "cellar") {:overlay "cellar_night";}
      :if (is_at "cellar_stairs") {:overlay "cellar_stairs_night";}
      :if (is_at "dining_room") {:overlay "dining_room_night";}
      :if (is_at "hallway_east") {:overlay "hallway_east_night";}
      :if (is_at "hallway_west") {:overlay "hallway_west_night";}
      :if (is_at "hotel_room") {:overlay "hotel_room_night";}
      :if (is_at "kitchen") {:overlay "kitchen_night";}
      :if (is_at "lobby") {:overlay "lobby_night";}
   }

   :if (is_at "cellar" && is_present "daniel") {:overlay "cellar_daniel";}
   :if (is_at "dining_room" && is_present "nora") {:overlay "dining_room_nora";}
   :if (is_at "hallway_east" && clock_hour == 3) {:overlay "clock_hour3";}
   :if (is_at "hallway_east" && clock_hour == 12) {:overlay "clock_hour12";}
   :if (is_at "kitchen" && is_present "haley") {:overlay "kitchen_haley";}
   :if (is_at "lobby" && is_present "joyce") {:overlay "lobby_joyce";}
}

on_describe {
   #
   # Description for objects, scenery, and NPCs
   #

   :if (is_present "daniel") {
      :if (!day1_daniel_met) {
         :set_true "day1_daniel_met";
         :print "A portly gentleman hunched over some equipment must be <Daniel<5>> like Joyce had mentioned.";
      } :else_if (!day1_daniel_done) {
         :print "<Daniel<5>> glances at you warily before going back to his equipment.";
      } :else {
         :print "<Daniel<5>> fusses with his equipment in the corner.";
      }
   }
   
   :if (is_present "haley") {
      :if (!day1_haley_met) {
         :set_true "day1_haley_met";
         :print "A young woman making tea must be Joyce's daughter <Haley<5>>. She nods at you curiously, but doesn't seem to object to your presence.";
      } :else_if (!day1_haley_done) {
         :print "<Haley<5>> makes tea and tries not to seem too curious about you.";
      } :else {
         :print "<Haley<5>> rummages about making tea.";
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "joyce") {
      :if (!day1_joyce_met) {
         :set_true "day1_joyce_met";
         :print "Behind the <front desk<5>> a woman beams at you with her best customer service smile. \"Welcome to the Red Soldier Inn!\", she proclaims, \"I'm <Joyce<5>>. How can I help you?\"";
      } :else_if (!day1_checkin_attempted) {
         :print "<Joyce<5>> continues to beam at you, though the amount of time you are taking seems to be making her somewhat nervous. \"Excuse me\", she says, \"can I help you?\"";
      } :else_if (!day1_checkin_done) {
         :print "<Joyce<5>> waits patiently for you to find your confirmation number.";
      } :else_if (!day1_joyce_done) {
         :set_true "day1_joyce_done";
         :print "<Joyce<5>> gives you a friendly wave. \"I hope you've settled in to your room? Do feel free to take a look around! We've got quite an historic beauty here. I'm sure Nora would love some company in the dining room! My daughter Haley is making her some tea. Daniel is off nosing about somewhere, I'm sure...\"";
      } :else_if (!day1_slept) {
         :print "<Joyce<5>> is doing paperwork behind the check-in desk.";
      } :else {
         :print "<Joyce<5>> is smiling, but clearly distressed. She must have seen the kitchen.";
      }
   }

   :if (is_holding "mobile_phone") {
      :if (!phone_read) {
         :if (!phone_buzzed) {
            :set_true "phone_buzzed";
            :print "Meanwhile, your <mobile phone<5>> buzzes with a notification.";
         } :else {
            :print "Also, your <phone<5>> buzzed recently, and you're itching to check it.";
         }
      } :else {
         :set_false "phone_buzzed";
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "nora") {
      :if (!day1_nora_met) {
         :set_true "day1_nora_met";
         :print "An older woman sitting at a table must be <Nora<5>>. \"Oh, hello!\" she says, \"you must be the new guest?\"";
      } :else_if (!day1_nora_done && is_carried "pamphlet") {
         :print "<Nora<5>> is visibly excited to see you holding the <pamphlet<5>> from the lobby.";
      } :else_if (!day1_slept) {
         :print "<Nora<5>> waits for her tea.";
      } :else_if (!day2_nora_scones) {
         :print "<Nora<5>> picks at her tea scones unhappily.";
      } :else {
         :print "<Nora<5>> savors her tea and scones.";
      }
   }

   #
   # Progress prompts
   #

   :if (!day1_slept && phone_read && day1_daniel_done && day1_haley_done && day1_nora_done) {
      :print "You're feeling sleepy. Maybe you should head to bed?";
   }
   
   :if (night1_awake && !night1_slept) {
      :if (is_carried "shirt_button" && !is_at "hotel_room") {
         :print "You're pretty tired and the mysterious ketchup vandal seems to be gone. Perhaps you should head back to bed.";
      } :else_if (sound_recorded && sound_played) {
         :print "You're seriously exhausted now. Maybe try to get some sleep?";
      }
   }
   
   :if (!day1_inventory_prompted) {
      :set_true "day1_inventory_prompted";
      :print "To look in your inventory, type <INV<5>>.";
   }
}

on_command {
   #
   # Commands for specific objects, scenery, and NPCs
   #

   :if (is_present "clock") {
      :match "look clock" {
          :print "This is a fine old <clock<5>>, but it seems to have stopped; it currently reads {clock_hour} o'clock.";
          :done;
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "creepy_message") {
      :match "look message" {
         :if (is_beside "shirt_button") {
            :print "You examine the message more closely. It smells like ketchup. Upon closer inspection, you notice something in one of the pools of ketchup dripping onto the counter. It appears to be a shirt button. That's odd. Do ghosts wear button down shirts? Impulsively, you pocket the button.";
            :pocket "shirt_button";
         } :else {
            :print "The creepy GET OUT message seems to be made of ketchup.";
         }
         :done;
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "daniel") {
      :if (!day1_daniel_done) {
         :match "look daniel" {
            :print "<Daniel<5>> is a rotund fellow with frizzy hair. He keeps almost saying something but thinking better of it.";
            :done;
         }

         :match "talk -;talk daniel" {
            :add_choice "Say hello" {
               :print "You say hello, startling the man out of his work.";
               :print "\"Can I help you?\" he asks. \"The washroom's over there if you're looking for it.\"";
               :press_any_key;
               :print "You explain you're staying at the inn, and realization comes over his face.";
               :print "\"Oh! Yeah, Joyce mentioned there would be another guest. I heard you were in the Captain's room. I had been using it for recordings, but...well, I guess it's good the hotel got new business.\"";
               :press_any_key;
               :print "He notices your quizzical look.";
               :print "\"Oh! I'm Daniel, by the way. I'm a ghost hunter. Uh, don't mind me, I'm just setting some stuff up for tonight.\"";
               :print "He goes back to his equipment.";
            }

            :add_choice "Ask Daniel about the equipment" {
               :print "\"Oh, this junk? This is kid stuff, but they wouldn't let me cross the border with the real gear.\"";
               :print "He never explains what it actually does, but you're starting to think that's just as well.";
            }

            :if (is_holding "pamphlet") {
               :add_choice "Show Daniel the pamphlet" {
                  :set_true "day1_daniel_done";
                  :print "Daniel almost looks annoyed when you show him the pamphlet.";
                  :print "\"She didn't even mention the hauntings here?! That's the most exciting thing about this inn! You would not believe the activity! I mean, you like ghost stories, don't you?\"";
                  :print "You do, and you say as much. Daniel seems pleased with this answer.";
                  :press_any_key;
                  :print "\"Hey...maybe you could help me out. I usually capture recordings in the Captain's room, where you're staying. I would hate to miss out on any activity. Think you could capture some for me? You can do it using this voice recorder! Any unusual noises, scratches, bumps, that sort of thing. There were rumours that there are voices, but I haven't heard them yet!\"";
                  :print "He hands you an analogue voice recorder. You take it nervously. You like a good ghost story, but do you want to be in one?";
                  :pocket "voice_recorder";
               }
            }
            :choose "What would you like to talk to Daniel about?";
            :done;
         }
      } :else {
         :match "look daniel" {
            :print "<Daniel<5>> is a rotund fellow with frizzy hair. He's frowning at his inscrutable equipment.";
            :done;
         }

         :match "talk -;talk daniel" {
            :print "Honestly, you'd rather not talk to Daniel any more than you have to.";
            :done;
         }
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "eerie_sound") {
      :match "listen sound;listen vent;listen -" {
         :set_sentence "examine eerie sound";
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "haley") {
      :if (!day1_haley_done) {
         :match "look haley" {
            :print "<Haley<5>> wears a button down uniform and a smirk only a teenager can perfect. She's making Nora's tea, which seems like a surprisingly complicated affair.";
            :done;
         }

         :match "talk -;talk haley" {
            :add_choice "Say hello" {
               :print "You greet Haley. She responds with a perky smile. She seems overly excited to see you here.";
               :print "\"Finally! We get a new guest! And one that isn't a total weirdo! Have you met Daniel by the way? He's a total weirdo. He's into all sorts of weird ghost stuff. Anyway, what brings you to town?\"";
               :press_any_key;
               :print "You explain that you are here for the local gaming convention. Haley's eyes grow even bigger.";
               :print "\"No way! You go to Gamecon! Aw man, I wish I could go, but I have to help mom out with the inn. It's not fair. If it weren't for Nora out there always needing scones, I could probably go!";
            }

            :add_choice "Ask Haley about Nora" {
               :print "\"Nora comes over every single day and always orders the exact same thing and if I don't make her tea scones perfectly she complains to Mom and I have to do them all over again!\" Haley rolls her eyes.";
               :press_any_key;
               :print "\"But Nora's sweet in her way I guess. Mom said Nora did a ton of research for that historical pamphlet, have you seen it? Don't tell Mom, but I haven't actually read it yet.\"";
            }

            :if (is_holding "pamphlet") {
               :add_choice "Show Haley the pamphlet" {
                  :set_true "day1_haley_done";
                  :print "\"So you saw mom's pamphlets! She'll be happy, she was really proud of those. Although she refused to mention the ghost.\"";
                  :press_any_key;
                  :print "She sees you raise your eyes.";
                  :print "\"What? You don't know about the ghost? I thought that's the only reason people would come here. And also the reason this place stays empty. If it wasn't for Daniel, we would be out of business. He's been here two months! Seriously, how is a bunch of knocks worth staying here two months?! If there is a ghost, it should be a proper ghost, like--\"";
                  :print "She makes a woooing sound and waves her arms around, then stops suddenly, looking worried.";
                  :press_any_key;
                  :print "\"Oh, crap. Hey, don't tell mom I told you about the ghost, okay? It stresses her out. You won't leave, right?\"";
                  :print "You assure her you won't.";
               }
            }
            :choose "What would you like to talk to Haley about?";
            :done;
         }
      } :else {
         :match "look haley" {
            :print "<Haley<5>> is a young woman in a button down uniform, focused intently on making Nora's tea.";
            :done;
         }

         :match "talk -;talk haley" {
            :print "You should probably let Haley finish making Nora's tea.";
            :done;
         }
      }
   }

   :if (is_present "hotel_bed") {
      :match "sleep -;sleep hotel_bed;goto sleep;goto hotel_bed;lie hotel_bed;lie down;use hotel_bed;bed -" {
         :if (!phone_read) {
